	annote = {Autobiogra-phies by authors from Arab countries are usually meant to win a battle (often political) with someone, to give a different account of events, to describe the author’s prowess in one or more areas of life. The author’s self remains carefully hidden. The self, the inner, secret self, is something a man (or a woman) in our region does not write about.
