(124)},
	annote = {male authors of autobiogra-phy avoid writing about the inner self. Men in a patriarchal society divided by class are accus-tomed to exercising power, to controlling, to constructing, to bringing order to chaos, to con-cealing weakness or replacing it with strength, and to molding things to their will. The self is a construction, an image that must be maintained. It is part of the order in which men live, and they are afraid that like any construction it might collapse.
124
