he reader—who completes the circuit by becoming an author herself.103 This model importantly traces how the economic and cultural conditions of print help determine that text's availability and potential for cultural impact: a physical book must be produced and distributed in order to be read, internalized, and potentially" (Brinkman 2016:45)
